==English==
===Noun===
'''[[dried]] [[plum]]''' (''plural'' '''dried plums''')

#(''US'') A [[prune]].

====Usage notes====
*'''Dried plum''' is used by some US companies that sell prunes in order to avoid the negative [[connotation]]s (such as laxative effects and consumption by the elderly) associated by some with the word ''prune''.<!--Source: Wikipedia article on "prune"-->